snippet.textDisplay: To be honest I feel this was the best song for coke studio's line up of 2017 and they gave it to RFAK as he's the most renowned singer in pak right now, that's where they missed the plot. There's not doubt that RFAK is an amazing singer but his voice is too classical for this song, Ali Noor's voice was really good. Sayyonnee or any other Junoon song can never be as good as the original just for the fact that the trio is no more together. I personally love Salman Ahmed for his guitar skills and the jugalbandi between electronic guitar and violin, that was epic.. fusion on eastern and western as he mentions. That was really really good.
